Profile

This individual is not a direct affiliate of the Berkley Center. They have contributed to one or more of our events, publications, or projects. Please contact the individual at their home institution.

Chelsea Clinton is vice chair of the Clinton Foundation, working with her parents, former president Bill Clinton and former secretary of state Hillary Rodham Clinton, to build partnerships across governments, NGOs, business, and individuals to further the vision and work of the Clinton Foundation. Chelsea Clintonâ€™s focus is on health programs, including the Clinton Health Care Access Initiative, the Alliance for a Healthier Generation, and the Clinton Health Matters Initiative, as well as empowering young people through the Clinton Global Initiative University and the Clinton Foundation Millennium Network. Apart from the foundation, Clinton is a special correspondent for NBC News. She has also worked at McKinsey & Company and Avenue Capital. Clinton earned a B.A. from Stanford University, M.Phil. from Oxford University, and M.P.H. from Columbia University's Mailman School of Public Health; she is currently pursuing a doctorate at Oxford.
